						<summary>

						<p>On the four faces of a broken slab lying in the Asharf-Khānā.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalla [Vikramāditya VI]. 11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This fragmentary and badly damaged record refers to Chālukya Tribhuvanamalladēva ruling from the capital Kalyāṇa and to his <hi rend="italic">mahāsāmatādhipati, mahāprachaṇḍa, daṇḍanāyaka</hi> Padmanābhayya. The latter was conferred with an administrative division (name lost) as <hi rend="italic">tribhōgābhyantarasiddhi</hi> by the king. It refers to the gift of an oil-mill and income from tolls. Details of the gifts including the donor and donee including the date are lost. It is in characters of about the 11th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
